gree within errors. Assuming values of clfar=4-9 from\nhydrodynamical models would imply a reduction of mass-loss rates included in\nstellar evolution models by a factor 2-3 for OSGs and by factors 6-200 for BSGs\nbelow the first bi-stability jump. This implies large reductions of mass-loss\nrates applied in evolution-models for BSGs, independently of the actual\nclumping properties of these winds, and a thorough re-investigation of BSG\nmass-loss rates and their effects on stellar evolution.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 26 Aug 2021 12:21:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-02-02"}
