evolutionary history, the compact\nobject in the system is more likely to have received a large natal kick, which\nsuggests that it is more likely a neutron star than a black hole.\nHD153919/4U1700-37 might be a prototype in the Milky Way for the progenitor of\ngravitational wave events such as GW190412\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 26 Aug 2021 14:02:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-11-17"}
